President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate L. Tammy Duckworth, director of the Illinois Department of Veterans Affairs, to be the Assistant Secretary of Public and Intergovernmental Affairs for the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA). Duckworth will be responsible for directing VA's public affairs, internal communications, and intergovernmental relations. She will also oversee programs for homeless Veterans, consumer affairs, and special rehabilitative events. Duckworth, a major in the Illinois National Guard, has personal experience as a wounded soldier and a strong commitment to Veterans. She has previously served in various roles, including as a logistics officer and company commander. Duckworth earned a bachelor's degree from the University of Hawaii and a master's degree from George Washington University. She is married to Iraq war Veteran and National Guard officer, Major Bryan Bowlsbey.